  "prompt": "Is walthpire.com a scam?",
  "response": "I don't have real-time browsing capabilities to check the current status of specific websites like walthpire.com. However, I can suggest some steps you can take to determine if a website is a scam:\n\n1. **Check Reviews**: Look for reviews of the website on third-party sites. Websites like Trustpilot, SiteJabber, or social media platforms can provide insight into other users' experiences.\n\n2. **Verify Contact Information**: A legitimate website usually has clear and accessible contact information. Check if they provide a phone number, email, and physical address.\n\n3. **Look for Secure Transactions**: If the website involves transactions, check if it uses HTTPS in the URL, indicating a secure connection.\n\n4. **Search for Red Flags**: Look for poor website design, excessive pop-up ads, or grammar and spelling errors, which can sometimes indicate a scam.\n\n5. **Check Domain Age**: You can use WHOIS lookup services to see how long the website has been active. New domains can sometimes be a red flag.\n\n6. **Consult Scam Alert Websites**: Websites like the Better Business Bureau (BBB) or other consumer protection sites can provide information on whether a website has been reported for scams.\n\nIf you have any specific experiences or more details about the site, feel free to share, and I can provide more tailored advice!",
